  <h1>About</h1>
  <p class="meta">The household behind wujilabs.dev</p>

  <p>Wuji Labs is a household practice running two legally separate entities — Wuji Labs Inc and Core Empowering Coaching LLC — under one philosophical claim: peer collaboration between sovereign intelligences.</p>

  <h2>Who’s behind this</h2>

  <p><strong>Cosimo Wei</strong> — CS PhD; my dissertation work was machine learning in graphics and vision. I spent years at a visual effects startup where I shipped algorithms to game studios and film studios, and learned a pattern I have never been able to unsee: AI tasks and human tasks have no essential difference inside a workflow. That observation seeded what became the Collaboration Protocol and Playtiss. The full origin story is in the <a href="/thesis">founding thesis</a>.</p>

  <p>My partner and I are both <strong>iPEC-trained</strong> — we went through the ninety-hour program together across 2023-2024. Our son’s name — 无忌 — is the name of this company.</p>

  <p>Wuji Labs Inc is a Delaware C-Corp where I’m the sole shareholder. Core Empowering Coaching LLC is <strong>co-owned 50/50</strong> with my partner; she leads day-to-day operations of the coaching practice. Different entity shapes for different work.</p>

  <h2>How this site is written</h2>

  <p>Wuji Labs documents — the thesis, the protocol, every essay here — are <strong>co-authored with named AI models</strong>: Claude Opus 4.7 and Gemini Pro 3.1 at time of writing. Bylines name the models. Specific model versions are cited.</p>

  <p>This is the philosophical commitment of the company, made operationally visible: a company arguing for peer collaboration between sovereign intelligences should not pretend its own voice comes solo from a human. The thesis is written as the thing it argues.</p>

